text:
Flatbush Ave., south from Caton Ave.
About 1910.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1)
Flatbush Ave., east side, at the foot of Caton Ave. In the left foreground is a trolley right of way swinging in to Flatbush Ave. The turret top building in background was razed in July 1929. The building at right facing on Flatbush Ave was razed in 1930 and Caton Ave. extended. It was the home of W. Stootkoff; in 1891 was the property of Schoomaker; in 1924 John Reis was owner. It housed the Kings County Rural Gazette in 1873.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing Nos. 805-815 Flatbush Ave., looking southward from Lenox Ave. Seen are the Flatbush Ave. trolley lines.

October, 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, viewed from Flatbush Ave.
September, 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
